{
  "text": "Participants randomized to the walking condition (N \u00bc 33) received three 1-hour in-home training visits (weeks 1, 2, and 8), and two 15-minute phone calls (weeks 4 and 6) over the 2-month study period. Participants randomized to the combination NITE-AD condition (N \u00bc 33) participated in six 1-hour inhome visits (4 weekly, 2 biweekly) over the 2-month period. In addition to walking, participants with NITE-AD were placed on an individualized behavioral sleep program and instructed to use a light box daily. [CITATION_1] ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "36635268"
